one_reviews_text: this is actually the worst thing i have ever seen all you can do is walk around and look at stuff thats it
IT'S NOT ONLY USELESS, IT'S JUST BAD.  360 PICTURE, NOT VR

With several different static viewpoints to choose from, you get to explore a virtual luxury loft in what looks like a very busy city.  The music is polite and beautiful, which is the nicest feature of the app. Because seriously, it is a very simple demo of a single home with a limited number of 360 photos in which to view it. That's it! If you're looking for a better experience along the real estate tract, please check out Realvision VR - they have at least 20 homes to choose from.

I thought this would be cool, but it's not even worth it to do a review. 
I'm just putting one star here, and you can download it and see exactly why I did this.

I don't see any reason for this to be pre-rendered. I have seen several realtime archviz VR demos using UE4 that looking much better than this. There are very limited viewpoints to teleport too. In general it's very forgettable and has a lot of warping issues due to it being stereo cubemap views with no positional tracking or head/neck model.
Graphically this looks impressive enough, but it's nothing more than a tech demo for spruiking stuff.  Do we really want the Oculus store to become a flood of advertising rubbish?
A couple of different view points, no positional tracking, which would slightly help with that minute, but awful image warps. Ah, also - VR watermarks galore! That's original, if I'm not mistaken.
Impressed, but positional tracking would help out.
What is this even doing here? This belongs at some real-estate website. All it does is waste bandwidth.
One of the worst experiences I had on the oculus home store. No positional tracking wich is very unconfortable and not that graphicaly impressive. Stay away
